HEADWORD: Oilseed
<hw>Oil"seed`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>Seed from which oil is expressed, as the castor bean;
also, the plant yielding such seed. See <er>Castor bean</er>.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>A cruciferous herb (<spn>Camelina sativa</spn>).</def>
<sd>(c)</sd> <def>The sesame.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>oil-silk</ent>⟦br⟧
